item.description:
Includes names and labels for the UOM, as well as details of vocabulary Lists that include the label, and defnitions.
             This can be a standard UOM such as SI units; or might be a relative/local measurement. An example of the latter is:

	PARAM name: field-based surface turbidity measure;
	PARAM defn:   visibility test taken at 1,3 aand 5 feet below surface;
	PARAM UOM:   possible value range is 10-0, 0 means clear;

Test involves visible detection of an item at 1, 3, and 5 feet, under the water surface.  The item placed under the water is a plate inscribed with a shape enclosing 4 dots; and that shape is of varying sizes.
